      "rationale": "Primary model inputs (geometry, rotational speed, flow rate boundary conditions) are well-characterized with uncertainty < 2%. Blood viscosity is identified as the key uncertain input: patient hematocrit variability (30–45%) produces a ±12% range in dynamic viscosity, which propagates to ±9% uncertainty in predicted RH. This uncertainty is explicitly flagged and documented in the sensitivity analysis. Despite this wide bound, all RH predictions remain below the RH < 1 acceptance threshold with margin > 0.15 RH units at the worst-case operating point, supporting acceptance at MRL 2. The viscosity uncertainty is accepted as residual risk given the conservative acceptance margin.",
